    {
      "id": "846685c294c7e84cf0d3fc7b1b39fa0c4021375e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-12 23:32:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHmm, both IDIF and DOT_LUSTRE_SEQ were already being added into FLDB. which patch do you mean here? Could you please post here. Thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1f16201d0ce25603a849f3b8c8acb932c694e5b9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 10:59:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\niirc, you said IDIFs can't be in FLDB ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d62e478d6ca65230a351926127c512d4f2a36f2a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 12:22:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nyes, because IDIF might be in many OSTs, instead of only one, like IGIF. so we can not put it into FLDB.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bd4faf13018ec8c11cf07d51740d529126a04ce0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 14:01:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5fa8e39a0555cd09ee0f97ddfbe36539cb24aa2e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 16:00:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nstatic inline obd_seq fid_idif_seq(obd_id id, __u32 ost_idx)\n{\n        return FID_SEQ_IDIF | (ost_idx << 16) | ((id >> 32) & 0xffff);\n}\n\nmeaning there is straight mapping between ost_idx and specific range of sequences? of course, unless we insert them all into fldb on demand, the former will explode..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
